msgid "Open assessment settings"
msgstr "Open assessment settings"

msgid ""
"Start from Settings if you need to create or import a new assessment. This "
"area is intended for users who have the required chat settings authority."
msgstr ""
"Start from Settings if you need to create or import a new assessment. This "
"area is intended for users who have the required chat settings authority."

msgid "Use the New assessment action to open the import flow."
msgstr "Use the New assessment action to open the import flow."

msgid ""
"Existing assessments stay visible in the settings list for review or "
"cleanup."
msgstr ""
"Existing assessments stay visible in the settings list for review or "
"cleanup."

msgid "Load the metadata JSON"
msgstr "Load the metadata JSON"

msgid ""
"Upload the DHIS2 metadata JSON file for the assessment tool. The import "
"flow checks the file before it lets you continue."
msgstr ""
"Upload the DHIS2 metadata JSON file for the assessment tool. The import "
"flow checks the file before it lets you continue."

msgid "Only `.json` files are accepted in the import step."
msgstr "Only `.json` files are accepted in the import step."

msgid "Parsing warnings are shown before you import the assessment."
msgstr "Parsing warnings are shown before you import the assessment."

msgid "Review the detected program"
msgstr "Review the detected program"

msgid ""
"Use the review step to inspect the program, program stage, sections, data "
"elements, option sets, and indicators that were found in the JSON."
msgstr ""
"Use the review step to inspect the program, program stage, sections, data "
"elements, option sets, and indicators that were found in the JSON."

msgid "Use the Next button after you finish reviewing the metadata preview."
msgstr "Use the Next button after you finish reviewing the metadata preview."

msgid ""
"The preview step helps you catch missing or unexpected metadata before "
"import."
msgstr ""
"The preview step helps you catch missing or unexpected metadata before "
"import."

msgid "Assign organisation units"
msgstr "Assign organisation units"

msgid ""
"The next step asks you to select organisation units before the final import "
"action becomes available."
msgstr ""
"The next step asks you to select organisation units before the final import "
"action becomes available."

msgid "You must select at least one organisation unit before importing."
msgstr "You must select at least one organisation unit before importing."

msgid ""
"This selection is part of the guided import flow and is confirmed before "
"the final import action."
msgstr ""
"This selection is part of the guided import flow and is confirmed before "
"the final import action."

msgid "Import the assessment"
msgstr "Import the assessment"

msgid ""
"Use Import assessment to save the program to DHIS2 and then register the "
"local assessment record so it appears in the chat app."
msgstr ""
"Use Import assessment to save the program to DHIS2 and then register the "
"local assessment record so it appears in the chat app."

msgid ""
"If the DHIS2 save succeeds but the local save fails, the screen shows a "
"retry option for the local record."
msgstr ""
"If the DHIS2 save succeeds but the local save fails, the screen shows a "
"retry option for the local record."

msgid "After a successful import, the app returns you to the settings list."
msgstr "After a successful import, the app returns you to the settings list."

msgid "Confirm the assessment is available"
msgstr "Confirm the assessment is available"

msgid ""
"After import, check the settings list and then open Data Capture to confirm "
"the new active assessment is available for users."
msgstr ""
"After import, check the settings list and then open Data Capture to confirm "
"the new active assessment is available for users."

msgid "Active assessments appear in the data capture home screen."
msgstr "Active assessments appear in the data capture home screen."

msgid ""
"Use the assessment details view in settings if you need to inspect the "
"imported program metadata."
msgstr ""
"Use the assessment details view in settings if you need to inspect the "
"imported program metadata."

